{
  "texts": [
    "Since the major background is induced by v 2, examin- ing the Δ observable with varying v 2 while holding the expected CME signal constant, is of interest.",
    "The event shape engineering (ESE) method is performed based on the magnitude of the flow vector to possibly access the geometry of the initial participant.",
    "The ESE selection of events is not expected to affect the magnetic field when restricted to a specified narrow centrality.",
    "The different dependencies of the CME signal and background on v 2 ( q 2) can possibly be used to disentangle the CME signal from the background.",
    "Using the ESE method, the ALICE experiment showed that the CME fraction in the measured Δ is consistent with zero [134].Examining the Δ observable with varying magnetic field while keeping the v 2 relatively constant is also of interest."
  ]
}